**user**:
> How do I add a layer to a group in QGIS?
**assistant**:
> Here's how to add a layer to a group in QGIS:
> 
> **Step 1:** Start QGIS and go to the 'Layers' panel.
> 
> **Step 2:** Create a new group or select the group where you want to add the new layer.
> 
> **Step 3:** To create the new group, right click on an empty space in the Layers panel and select "Add group". A new group will be created; set the name of the group.
> 
> **Step 4:** After the new group or desired group is selected, either:
> 
> - Drag and drop the layer you want to add into the group; or, 
> - Right click on the layer -> select 'Move to group' -> select the desired group from the dropdown menu.
> 
> Now, your new layer has been placed in the group you selected.
> 
> Remember that with your cursor arrow, you can drag layers and groups to rearrange them. This gives you the flexibility to organize layers in the manner that best aids your work.
